HEADWORD: Grazier
<hw>Gra"zier</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One who pastures
cattle, and rears them for market.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The inhabitants be rather . . . <qex>graziers</qex> than
plowmen.</q> <rj><qau>Stow.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grazing</ent>⟦br⟧
